content: I think my total income for the month after taxes is around $4,000. My fixed expenses are rent ($1,500), utilities ($150), car payment ($300), and minimum credit card payments ($500). As for variable expenses, I spend around $500 on groceries, $200 on entertainment, and $100 on hobbies. I'm not really sure about travel expenses since I don't have any trips planned, but I do want to set aside some money for that. Miscellaneous expenses are usually around $100.
